    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Skiver, usually sheepskin, that has been coated with a thin paste or glue wash, which, when it dries, causes the skin to shrink and draw up, forming an artificial grain pattern which is then enhanced by boarding.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cuero ordinario, habitualmente de carnero, que ha sido revestido con una pasta delgada o un lavado de adhesivo que, al secarse, causa un encogimiento de la piel que forma un diseño de grano artificial, destacado al ponerlo sobre tapas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Skiver, meestal van schapenhuid, bewerkt met een dunne plak- of lijmlaag die na opdrogen het leer doet krimpen en stabiliseren. Zo ontstaat een kunstmatig korrelpatroon dat vervolgens wordt verrijkt door het te 'krispelen'.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>通常由綿羊皮製成的羊皮薄片，在羊皮上塗抹一層薄薄的漿或膠，待其乾燥後，便會使皮面收縮而緊靠，可形成人工紋理，可藉由搓紋而使紋理更好看。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
